          </p>
        </statement>
      </exercise>
      <exercise>
        <statement>
          <p>
            I need to draw a line on a diagram perpendicular to the line <m>y = \frac{3}{2}x - 5</m>.
            The diagram is on a grid,
            and so I can count units of rise and run from my starting point to make sure that my line has the appropriate slope.
            What should the rise be?
            What should the run be?
          </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
          <p>
            rise: <m>-2</m>, run: <m>+3</m> OR rise:
            <m>+2</m>, run: <m>-3</m>
          </p>
        </solution>
      </exercise>
